Exerceee and its tenses, exercitus and its cases, occur nearly forty times in Plautus, and in three of these exercitam and exerce'tu appear to have the first short. It is to be remarked that the whole of these examples are in the Amphitruo, and two of them within a few lines of each other in the Prologue-a portion of the play which contains a number of metrical licences within a short compass, and with regard to the genuineness of which some good scholars have enter- tained grave doubts.
